      <abstract>
        <p>We report 11 cases of severe <italic>Plasmodium vivax</italic> malaria in Bikaner (western India). Patients exhibited cerebral malaria, renal failure, circulatory collapse, severe anemia, hemoglobinurea, abnormal bleeding, acute respiratory distress syndrome, and jaundice. Peripheral blood microscopy, parasite antigen&#x2013;based assays, and parasite 18s rRNA gene&#x2013;based polymerase chain reaction showed the presence of <italic>P. vivax</italic> and absence of <italic>P. falciparum</italic>.</p>
      </abstract>
